var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#1D-Fourier-Transform","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"This tutorial demonstrates how to compute the discrete Fourier transform (DFT) of a function on an exponentially large quantics grid using Tensor4all.jl.  The key idea is that the DFT matrix itself admits a low-rank tensor train (QTT) representation, so the transform can be carried out entirely within the QTT framework – without ever constructing the full 2^R times 2^R DFT matrix.","title":"1D Fourier Transform"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Why-QTT-based-Fourier-transforms?","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"A standard DFT on M = 2^R points costs O(M log M) via FFT.  When R = 40, we have M approx 10^12 – a trillion points – and even the FFT becomes infeasible.  The QTT approach bypasses this: if the input function has a compact QTT representation (small bond dimension), and the DFT operator also has small bond dimension (it does), then the Fourier coefficients can be computed by a tensor-train contraction whose cost scales only with the bond dimensions, not with M.\n\nThis is particularly valuable when you need Fourier coefficients at specific frequencies (small k or large k) rather than the entire spectrum, since individual coefficients can be evaluated in O(R) time once the output QTT is available.","title":"Why QTT-based Fourier transforms?"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Setup","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"using Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids       # Grid types and coordinate conversions\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI         # quanticscrossinterpolate\nusing Tensor4all.SimpleTT            # to_tensor_train\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTN              # MPS, linkdims, ...\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform   # fourier_operator, set_iospaces!, apply\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTCI: evaluate as ttn_evaluate  # evaluate TTN at quantics index","title":"Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Problem:-Fourier-transform-of-a-sum-of-exponentials","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"We consider a function on 0 1 that mimics a bosonic correlator:\n\nf(x) = sum_p fracc_p1 - e^-varepsilon_p e^-varepsilon_p x\n\nwith parameters c_1 = 15, varepsilon_1 = 30, c_2 = 07, varepsilon_2 = 150.  This function varies rapidly near x = 0 (due to the varepsilon_2 = 15 term) and has a slow exponential tail, creating multi-scale structure ideally suited for quantics representation.\n\nc  = [1.5, 0.7]\neps = [3.0, 15.0]\n\nf(x) = Base.sum(c[p] * exp(-eps[p] * x) / (1 - exp(-eps[p])) for p in 1:2)\n\nnote: Note\nWe write Base.sum instead of sum because QuanticsTCI also exports a sum function.  Using the qualified name avoids ambiguity.","title":"Problem: Fourier transform of a sum of exponentials"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Step-1:-Quantics-cross-interpolation","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"Create a quantics grid with R = 40 bits (2^40 approx 10^12 points) and build the QTT approximation:\n\nR = 40\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid(1, R, [0.0], [1.0])\n\nci, ranks, errors = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; tolerance=1e-10)\n\nThe maximum bond dimension will be small (typically around 10–15), reflecting the low complexity of exponentials in the quantics representation.","title":"Step 1: Quantics cross-interpolation"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Step-2:-Convert-to-MPS","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"Convert the QTCI result to a TreeTensorNetwork (MPS) for use with the Fourier operator:\n\ntt = to_tensor_train(ci)   # SimpleTensorTrain\nfmps = MPS(tt)             # TreeTensorNetwork{Int}","title":"Step 2: Convert to MPS"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Step-3:-Construct-and-apply-the-Fourier-operator","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"The fourier_operator function creates the QTT representation of the DFT matrix with the convention\n\nhatf_k = frac1sqrtM sum_m=0^M-1 f_m e^-2pi i k m  M\nqquad M = 2^R\n\nBefore applying the operator, its site indices must be bound to those of the input MPS via set_iospaces!:\n\nft_op = fourier_operator(R; forward=true)\nset_iospaces!(ft_op, fmps)\nhfmps = apply(ft_op, fmps; method=:naive)\n\ntip: Tip\nThe method=:naive contraction is the simplest and works well when bond dimensions are moderate.  For larger problems, :zipup or :fit can reduce the bond dimension of the result at the cost of a controlled approximation error.","title":"Step 3: Construct and apply the Fourier operator"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Step-4:-Evaluate-Fourier-coefficients","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"To evaluate hatf_k at a specific frequency index k, convert k to its binary (quantics) representation and call ttn_evaluate:\n\nk = 5\nbits = digits(k, base=2, pad=R)   # LSB-first bit vector, length R\nval = ttn_evaluate(hfmps, bits)\n\nThe digits function returns the bits in LSB-first order, which is the correct convention for ttn_evaluate – no reversal is needed.\n\nnote: Note\nThe result hfmps from apply is a TreeTensorNetwork that may not satisfy is_chain(hfmps).  Always use ttn_evaluate to read out values, rather than assuming a chain topology.","title":"Step 4: Evaluate Fourier coefficients"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Step-5:-Compare-with-the-analytical-DFT","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"Each exponential term g_p(x) = c_p  (1 - e^-varepsilon_p) e^-varepsilon_p x sampled at x = mM gives a geometric series in the DFT.  The exact discrete Fourier coefficient is:\n\nhatf_k = frac1sqrtM sum_p\n  fracc_p1 - e^-varepsilon_p\n  cdot frac1 - e^-(varepsilon_p + 2pi i k)1 - e^-(varepsilon_p + 2pi i k)M\n\nThis follows from summing the geometric series sum_m=0^M-1 r^m = (1 - r^M)(1 - r) with r = e^-(varepsilon_p + 2pi i k)M.\n\nIn Julia:\n\nM = 2^R\n\nfunction analytical_dft(k)\n    result = zero(ComplexF64)\n    for p in 1:2\n        z = eps[p] + 2π * im * k\n        geom = (1 - exp(-z)) / (1 - exp(-z / M))\n        result += c[p] / (1 - exp(-eps[p])) * geom\n    end\n    return result / sqrt(M)\nend\n\nCheck the accuracy at a few frequencies:\n\nfor k in [0, 1, 5, 100]\n    bits = digits(k, base=2, pad=R)\n    qft_val = ttn_evaluate(hfmps, bits)\n    exact_val = analytical_dft(k)\n    rel_err = abs(qft_val - exact_val) / abs(exact_val)\n    println(\"k = $k:  QFT = $qft_val,  exact = $exact_val,  rel_err = $rel_err\")\nend","title":"Step 5: Compare with the analytical DFT"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#High-frequency-accuracy","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"A major advantage of the QTT Fourier transform is access to high-frequency coefficients at no additional cost.  Evaluating hatf_10000 is just as cheap as evaluating hatf_1:\n\nfor k in [10, 100, 1000, 10000]\n    bits = digits(k, base=2, pad=R)\n    qft_val = ttn_evaluate(hfmps, bits)\n    exact_val = analytical_dft(k)\n    rel_err = abs(qft_val - exact_val) / abs(exact_val)\n    println(\"k = $k:  rel_err = $rel_err\")\nend\n\nWith tolerance 10^-10 in the QTCI step, relative errors are typically 10^-10 or better across all frequencies.","title":"High-frequency accuracy"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Complete-example","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"Putting it all together:\n\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI\nusing Tensor4all.SimpleTT\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTN\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTCI: evaluate as ttn_evaluate\n\n# Parameters\nc   = [1.5, 0.7]\neps = [3.0, 15.0]\nR   = 40\nM   = 2^R\n\n# Target function\nf(x) = Base.sum(c[p] * exp(-eps[p] * x) / (1 - exp(-eps[p])) for p in 1:2)\n\n# 1. QTCI on a trillion-point grid\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid(1, R, [0.0], [1.0])\nci, ranks, errors = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; tolerance=1e-10)\n\n# 2. Convert to MPS\ntt = to_tensor_train(ci)\nfmps = MPS(tt)\n\n# 3. Apply Fourier operator\nft_op = fourier_operator(R; forward=true)\nset_iospaces!(ft_op, fmps)\nhfmps = apply(ft_op, fmps; method=:naive)\n\n# 4. Analytical reference (exact geometric series)\nfunction analytical_dft(k)\n    result = zero(ComplexF64)\n    for p in 1:2\n        z = eps[p] + 2π * im * k\n        geom = (1 - exp(-z)) / (1 - exp(-z / M))\n        result += c[p] / (1 - exp(-eps[p])) * geom\n    end\n    return result / sqrt(M)\nend\n\n# 5. Compare at low and high k\nfor k in [0, 1, 5, 100, 10000]\n    bits = digits(k, base=2, pad=R)\n    qft_val = ttn_evaluate(hfmps, bits)\n    exact_val = analytical_dft(k)\n    rel_err = abs(qft_val - exact_val) / abs(exact_val)\n    println(\"k = $k:  rel_err = $(round(rel_err, sigdigits=2))\")\nend","title":"Complete example"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#The-pipeline-at-a-glance","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"The overall workflow is:\n\nf(x)  →  QTCI  →  MPS  →  Fourier operator × MPS  →  evaluate at k\n\nEach step is efficient: the QTCI scales with bond dimension, not grid size; the Fourier operator has O(1) bond dimension per site; the contraction is a standard tensor-train operation; and pointwise evaluation costs O(R).","title":"The pipeline at a glance"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#API-summary","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"Function Description\nquanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; tolerance) Build QTT via cross-interpolation\nto_tensor_train(ci) Convert QTCI result to SimpleTensorTrain\nMPS(tt) Convert SimpleTensorTrain to TreeTensorNetwork{Int}\nfourier_operator(R; forward=true) Create QTT Fourier operator (LinearOperator)\nset_iospaces!(op, mps) Bind operator site indices to the input MPS\napply(op, mps; method=:naive) Apply operator to MPS, return TreeTensorNetwork\nttn_evaluate(ttn, bits) Evaluate TTN at a quantics bit vector\ndigits(k, base=2, pad=R) Convert integer k to LSB-first bit vector","title":"API summary"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/fourier1d/#Normalization-convention","page":"1D Fourier Transform","text":"The forward Fourier operator implements:\n\nhatf_k = frac1sqrtM sum_m=0^M-1 f_m e^-2pi i k m  M\n\nThis is the symmetric convention with 1sqrtM normalization and a negative sign in the exponent.  When comparing with analytical results, ensure your reference formula uses the same convention.","title":"Normalization convention"},{"category":"section","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#QuanticsGrids","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"","title":"QuanticsGrids"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"DiscretizedGrid\n\nA discretized grid with continuous domain and floating-point coordinates.\n\nConstructors\n\nDiscretizedGrid(ndims, R, lower, upper; unfolding=:fused) - uniform R\nDiscretizedGrid(ndims, rs, lower, upper; unfolding=:fused) - per-dimension R\n\nProperties\n\nndims(g) - Number of dimensions\nrs(g) - Resolution (bits) per dimension\nlocal_dimensions(g) - Local dimensions of tensor sites\nlower_bound(g) - Lower bounds per dimension\nupper_bound(g) - Upper bounds per dimension\ngrid_step(g) - Grid spacing per dimension\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid-Tuple{Int64, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Real}, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"DiscretizedGrid(ndims::Int, rs::Vector{Int}, lower, upper; unfolding=:fused)\n\nCreate a DiscretizedGrid with per-dimension resolutions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid-Tuple{Int64, Int64, AbstractVector{<:Real}, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"DiscretizedGrid(ndims::Int, R::Int, lower, upper; unfolding=:fused)\n\nCreate a DiscretizedGrid with uniform resolution R for all dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"InherentDiscreteGrid\n\nA discrete grid for quantics tensor train representations with integer coordinates.\n\nConstructors\n\nInherentDiscreteGrid(ndims, R; origin=nothing, unfolding=:fused) - uniform R\nInherentDiscreteGrid(ndims, rs; origin=nothing, unfolding=:fused) - per-dimension R\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid-Tuple{Int64, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"InherentDiscreteGrid(ndims::Int, rs::Vector{Int}; origin=nothing, unfolding=:fused)\n\nCreate an InherentDiscreteGrid with per-dimension resolutions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"InherentDiscreteGrid(ndims::Int, R::Int; origin=nothing, unfolding=:fused)\n\nCreate an InherentDiscreteGrid with uniform resolution R.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.InherentDiscreteGrid"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Base.ndims-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"ndims(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Int\n\nNumber of dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.ndims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grid_step-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"grid_step(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nGrid spacing per dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grid_step"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grididx_to_origcoord-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"grididx_to_origcoord(g::DiscretizedGrid, grididx) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nConvert grid indices (1-indexed) to original coordinates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grididx_to_origcoord"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grididx_to_quantics-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"grididx_to_quantics(g::DiscretizedGrid, grididx) -> Vector{Int64}\n\nConvert grid indices to quantics indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.grididx_to_quantics"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.local_dimensions-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"local_dimensions(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Vector{Int}\n\nLocal dimensions of all tensor sites.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.local_dimensions"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.lower_bound-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"lower_bound(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nLower bounds per dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.lower_bound"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origcoord_to_grididx-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"origcoord_to_grididx(g::DiscretizedGrid, coord) -> Vector{Int64}\n\nConvert original coordinates to grid indices (1-indexed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origcoord_to_grididx"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origcoord_to_quantics-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"origcoord_to_quantics(g::DiscretizedGrid, coord) -> Vector{Int64}\n\nConvert original (continuous) coordinates to quantics indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origcoord_to_quantics"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origin-Tuple{InherentDiscreteGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"origin(g::InherentDiscreteGrid) -> Vector{Int64}\n\nOrigin per dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.origin"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.quantics_to_grididx-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"quantics_to_grididx(g::DiscretizedGrid, quantics) -> Vector{Int64}\n\nConvert quantics indices to grid indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.quantics_to_grididx"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.quantics_to_origcoord-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"quantics_to_origcoord(g::DiscretizedGrid, quantics) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nConvert quantics indices to original (continuous) coordinates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.quantics_to_origcoord"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.rs-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"rs(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Vector{Int}\n\nResolution (bits) per dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.rs"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticsgrids/#Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.upper_bound-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid}","page":"QuanticsGrids","text":"upper_bound(g::DiscretizedGrid) -> Vector{Float64}\n\nUpper bounds per dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids.upper_bound"},{"category":"section","location":"api/core/#Core:-Index,-Tensor,-Algorithm","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"","title":"Core: Index, Tensor, Algorithm"},{"category":"section","location":"api/core/#Index","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"","title":"Index"},{"category":"section","location":"api/core/#Tensor","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"","title":"Tensor"},{"category":"section","location":"api/core/#Storage-Kinds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"","title":"Storage Kinds"},{"category":"section","location":"api/core/#Algorithm","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"","title":"Algorithm"},{"category":"type","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.Index","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"Index\n\nA tensor index with dimension, ID, and tags.\n\nWraps a Rust DynIndex (= Index<DynId, TagSet>) which corresponds to ITensors.jl's Index{Int} (no quantum number symmetry).\n\nConstructors\n\nIndex(dim::Integer) - Create index with dimension\nIndex(dim::Integer; tags::AbstractString) - Create with tags\nIndex(dim::Integer, id::UInt64; tags::AbstractString) - Create with specific ID\n\nProperties\n\ndim(i::Index) - Get the dimension\nid(i::Index) - Get the unique ID as UInt64\ntags(i::Index) - Get tags as comma-separated string\nhastag(i::Index, tag::AbstractString) - Check if index has a tag\nplev(i::Index) - Get the prime level\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.Index"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.dim","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"dim(i::Index) -> Int\n\nGet the dimension of an index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.dim"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.tags","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"tags(i::Index) -> String\n\nGet the tags of an index as a comma-separated string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.tags"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.id","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"id(i::Index) -> UInt64\n\nGet the unique ID of an index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.id"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.hastag","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"hastag(i::Index, tag::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nCheck if an index has a specific tag.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.hastag"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.plev","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"plev(i::Index) -> Int\n\nGet the prime level of an index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.plev"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.sim","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"sim(i::Index) -> Index\n\nCreate a new index with the same dimension and tags but a new unique ID. This is useful for creating \"similar\" indices that won't contract with the original.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.sim"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.prime","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"prime(i::Index, n::Integer=1) -> Index\n\nReturn a copy of the index with prime level incremented by n.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.prime"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.noprime","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"noprime(i::Index) -> Index\n\nReturn a copy of the index with prime level set to 0.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.noprime"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.setprime","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"setprime(i::Index, n::Integer) -> Index\n\nReturn a copy of the index with prime level set to n.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.setprime"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.hasind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"hasind(i::Index) -> Function\n\nReturn a function that checks if its argument has the index i.\n\nExample\n\nsites = [Index(2), Index(3)]\ntt = random_tt(sites; linkdims=2)\nfindfirst(hasind(sites[1]), tt)  # Returns 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.hasind"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.hasinds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"hasinds(is) -> Function\n\nReturn a function that checks if its argument has all the indices in is.\n\nExample\n\ni, j = Index(2), Index(3)\nt = Tensor([i, j], rand(2, 3))\nhasinds([i, j])(t)  # true\nhasinds([i])(t)     # true\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.hasinds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.hascommoninds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"hascommoninds(inds1, inds2) -> Bool\n\nCheck if two collections of indices have any common indices.\n\nExample\n\ni, j, k = Index(2), Index(3), Index(4)\nhascommoninds([i, j], [j, k])  # true\nhascommoninds([i], [k])        # false\n\n\n\n\n\nhascommoninds(is::Vector{Index}) -> HasCommonIndsPredicate\n\nReturn a predicate that checks if its argument has common indices with is. Useful for findfirst, findall, etc.\n\nExample\n\nsites = [Index(2), Index(3), Index(4)]\ntt = random_tt(sites; linkdims=2)\nfindfirst(hascommoninds(sites[2:2]), tt)  # Returns 2\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.hascommoninds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.commoninds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"commoninds(inds1, inds2) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReturn the indices that appear in both collections. Returns indices from inds1.\n\nExample\n\ni, j, k = Index(2), Index(3), Index(4)\ncommoninds([i, j], [j, k])  # [j]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.commoninds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.commonind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"commonind(inds1, inds2) -> Union{Index, Nothing}\n\nReturn the first common index, or nothing if none exists.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.commonind"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.common_inds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"commoninds(inds1, inds2) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReturn the indices that appear in both collections. Returns indices from inds1.\n\nExample\n\ni, j, k = Index(2), Index(3), Index(4)\ncommoninds([i, j], [j, k])  # [j]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.common_inds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.uniqueinds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"uniqueinds(inds1, inds2) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReturn the indices in inds1 that do not appear in inds2.\n\nExample\n\ni, j, k = Index(2), Index(3), Index(4)\nuniqueinds([i, j], [j, k])  # [i]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.uniqueinds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.uniqueind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"uniqueind(inds1, inds2) -> Union{Index, Nothing}\n\nReturn the first unique index in inds1 (not in inds2), or nothing if none exists.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.uniqueind"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.noncommoninds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"noncommoninds(inds1, inds2) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReturn all indices that appear in only one of the collections. Equivalent to union of uniqueinds(inds1, inds2) and uniqueinds(inds2, inds1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.noncommoninds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.replaceinds","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"replaceinds(inds, old_inds, new_inds) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReplace indices in inds according to the mapping oldinds → newinds.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.replaceinds"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.replaceind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"replaceind(inds, old_ind, new_ind) -> Vector{Index}\n\nReplace a single index in inds.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.replaceind"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.onehot","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"onehot(ivs::Pair{Index,<:Integer}...)\n\nCreate a one-hot tensor with value 1.0 at the specified index positions. Compatible with ITensors.jl's onehot(i => 1, j => 2).\n\nUses 1-based indexing (converted to 0-based internally for Rust).\n\nExamples\n\ni = Index(3)\nj = Index(4)\nA = onehot(i => 1)           # A[i=>1] == 1.0\nB = onehot(i => 2, j => 3)   # B[i=>2,j=>3] == 1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.onehot"},{"category":"type","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.Tensor","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"Tensor\n\nA tensor with dynamically-typed indices and storage.\n\nWraps a Rust TensorDynLen which corresponds to ITensors.jl's ITensor.\n\nConstructors\n\nTensor(indices::Vector{Index}, data::Array{Float64}) - Create dense f64 tensor\nTensor(indices::Vector{Index}, data::Array{ComplexF64}) - Create dense complex tensor\n\nProperties\n\nrank(t::Tensor) - Get the number of indices\ndims(t::Tensor) - Get dimensions as a tuple\nindices(t::Tensor) - Get indices as a vector\nstorage_kind(t::Tensor) - Get the storage kind (DenseF64, DenseC64, etc.)\ndata(t::Tensor) - Get the tensor data as an Array\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.Tensor"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.rank","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"rank(t::Tensor) -> Int\n\nGet the number of indices (rank) of a tensor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.rank"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.dims","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"dims(t::Tensor) -> NTuple{N, Int}\n\nGet the dimensions of a tensor as a tuple.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.dims"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.indices","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"indices(t::Tensor) -> Vector{Index}\n\nGet the indices of a tensor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.indices"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.data","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"data(t::Tensor) -> Array\n\nGet the tensor data as a column-major Julia array.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.data"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.storage_kind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"storage_kind(t::Tensor) -> StorageKind\n\nGet the storage kind of a tensor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.storage_kind"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.contract","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"contract(a::TreeTensorNetwork, b::TreeTensorNetwork; kwargs...) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nContract two tree tensor networks.\n\nArguments\n\nmethod: Contraction method - :zipup (default), :fit, or :naive\nmaxdim: Maximum bond dimension (0 for no limit)\nrtol: Relative tolerance (0.0 = not set)\ncutoff: ITensorMPS.jl cutoff (0.0 = not set)\n\n\n\n\n\ncontract(t1::Tensor, t2::Tensor) -> Tensor\n\nContract two tensors by matching common indices (same ID + tags + plev). Returns a new tensor with the non-contracted indices from both inputs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.contract"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.diag_embed","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"diag_embed(t::Tensor, idx::Index) -> Tensor\n\nCreate a new tensor where idx is duplicated as prime(idx). The result is diagonal in idx and prime(idx): only elements where idx == prime(idx) are nonzero.\n\nThis is used to convert MPS-like site tensors to MPO-like site tensors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.diag_embed"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.diag_trace","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"diag_trace(t::Tensor, idx::Index, idx_prime::Index) -> Tensor\n\nExtract the diagonal of a tensor in idx and idx_prime, keeping only idx. This is the inverse of diag_embed: it reduces an MPO-like site tensor back to MPS-like by tracing out the primed index.\n\nRequires dim(idx) == dim(idx_prime).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.diag_trace"},{"category":"type","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.StorageKind","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"StorageKind\n\nEnum representing the storage type of a tensor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.StorageKind"},{"category":"module","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.Algorithm","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"Algorithm\n\nSubmodule for algorithm selection types (corresponds to tensor4all-core-common).\n\nProvides enum-like types for selecting algorithms in various tensor operations, following patterns from ITensors.jl.\n\nBasic Usage\n\nusing Tensor4all.Algorithm\n\n# Factorization algorithms\nalg = FactorizeAlgorithm.SVD\nalg = FactorizeAlgorithm.LU\n\n# Contraction algorithms\nalg = ContractionAlgorithm.Naive\nalg = ContractionAlgorithm.ZipUp\n\n# Compression algorithms\nalg = CompressionAlgorithm.SVD\nalg = CompressionAlgorithm.Variational\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.Algorithm"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.Algorithm.get_default_svd_rtol","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"get_default_svd_rtol()\n\nGet the default SVD relative tolerance from the Rust library.\n\nThis is the default value used for truncation when no tolerance is specified.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.Algorithm.get_default_svd_rtol"},{"category":"function","location":"api/core/#Tensor4all.Algorithm.resolve_truncation_tolerance","page":"Core (Index, Tensor)","text":"resolve_truncation_tolerance(; cutoff=nothing, rtol=nothing)\n\nResolve truncation tolerance from cutoff (ITensor style) or rtol (tensor4all style).\n\nArguments\n\ncutoff: ITensor-style squared error tolerance: Σ_{discarded} σ²ᵢ / Σᵢ σ²ᵢ ≤ cutoff\nrtol: tensor4all-style relative Frobenius error: ‖A - Aapprox‖F / ‖A‖_F ≤ rtol\n\nReturns\n\nThe effective rtol value.\n\nConversion\n\ncutoff = rtol², so rtol = √cutoff\n\nBehavior\n\nIf neither specified: returns the default rtol from Rust\nIf only cutoff specified: returns √cutoff\nIf only rtol specified: returns rtol\nIf both specified: throws an error\n\nExamples\n\n# Use default\nrtol = resolve_truncation_tolerance()\n\n# ITensor style\nrtol = resolve_truncation_tolerance(cutoff=1e-24)  # returns 1e-12\n\n# tensor4all style\nrtol = resolve_truncation_tolerance(rtol=1e-12)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.Algorithm.resolve_truncation_tolerance"},{"category":"section","location":"api/quanticstci/#QuanticsTCI","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"","title":"QuanticsTCI"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"QuanticsTensorCI2\n\nA Quantics TCI (Tensor Cross Interpolation) object.\n\nThis wraps the Rust QuanticsTCI and provides access to the interpolated quantics tensor train representation of a function.\n\nMethods\n\nrank(qtci) - Get the maximum bond dimension\nlink_dims(qtci) - Get the link (bond) dimensions\nevaluate(qtci, indices) - Evaluate at grid indices\nsum(qtci) - Compute the factorized sum over all grid points\nintegral(qtci) - Compute the integral over the continuous domain\nto_tensor_train(qtci) - Convert to SimpleTensorTrain\n\nCallable Interface\n\nThe object can be called directly with indices:\n\nqtci(1, 2)  # Equivalent to evaluate(qtci, [1, 2])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.evaluate-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2, Vector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"evaluate(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2, indices::Vector{<:Integer}) -> Float64\n\nEvaluate the QTCI at the given grid indices (1-indexed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.evaluate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.integral-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"integral(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2) -> Float64\n\nCompute the integral over the continuous domain.\n\nThis is the sum multiplied by the grid step sizes. Only meaningful for QTCI constructed with a DiscretizedGrid. For discrete grids, this returns the plain sum.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.integral"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.link_dims-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"link_dims(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2) -> Vector{Int}\n\nGet the link (bond) dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.link_dims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.quanticscrossinterpolate-Tuple{DiscretizedGrid, Any}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"quanticscrossinterpolate(grid::DiscretizedGrid, f; kwargs...) -> QuanticsTensorCI2\n\nPerform quantics cross interpolation on a continuous domain.\n\nArguments\n\ngrid: DiscretizedGrid describing the domain\nf: Function that takes Float64 coordinates and returns Float64\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ntolerance: Convergence tolerance (default: 1e-8)\nmax_bonddim: Maximum bond dimension, 0 = unlimited (default: 0)\nmax_iter: Maximum iterations (default: 200)\n\nExample\n\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI\n\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid(1, 10, [0.0], [1.0])\nqtci = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, x -> sin(x))\nintegral(qtci)  # Should be close to 1 - cos(1) ~ 0.4597\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.quanticscrossinterpolate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.quanticscrossinterpolate_discrete-Tuple{Vector{<:Integer}, Any}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"quanticscrossinterpolate_discrete(sizes, f; kwargs...) -> QuanticsTensorCI2\n\nPerform quantics cross interpolation on a discrete integer domain.\n\nArguments\n\nsizes: Grid sizes per dimension (must be powers of 2)\nf: Function that takes 1-indexed integer indices and returns Float64\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ntolerance: Convergence tolerance (default: 1e-8)\nmax_bonddim: Maximum bond dimension, 0 = unlimited (default: 0)\nmax_iter: Maximum iterations (default: 200)\nunfoldingscheme: :interleaved or :fused (default: :interleaved)\n\nExample\n\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI\n\nqtci = quanticscrossinterpolate_discrete([8, 8], (i, j) -> Float64(i + j))\nqtci(3, 4)  # Should be close to 7.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.quanticscrossinterpolate_discrete"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.rank-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"rank(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2) -> Int\n\nGet the maximum bond dimension (rank).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.rank"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.sum-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"sum(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2) -> Float64\n\nCompute the factorized sum over all grid points.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.sum"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstci/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.to_tensor_train-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.QuanticsTensorCI2}","page":"QuanticsTCI","text":"to_tensor_train(qtci::QuanticsTensorCI2) -> SimpleTensorTrain\n\nConvert the QTCI to a SimpleTensorTrain.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI.to_tensor_train"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Module-Architecture","page":"Modules","text":"","title":"Module Architecture"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Dependency-Graph","page":"Modules","text":"                    ┌──────────────────────┐\n                    │   Core Foundation     │\n                    │  Index, Tensor,       │\n                    │  Algorithm            │\n                    └──────────┬───────────┘\n                               │\n               ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n               ▼               ▼               ▼\n         ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────────┐\n         │ SimpleTT │◄─►│  TreeTN  │   │QuanticsGrids │\n         │          │   │ MPS/MPO  │   │              │\n         └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └──────┬───────┘\n                             │                 │\n                    ┌────────┼────────┐        │\n                    ▼        ▼        ▼        ▼\n              ┌──────────┐ ┌──────┐ ┌────────────┐\n              │Quantics  │ │Tree  │ │QuanticsTCI │\n              │Transform │ │TCI   │ │            │\n              └──────────┘ └──────┘ └────────────┘","title":"Dependency Graph"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Data-Flow","page":"Modules","text":"Tensor4all.jl modules form a pipeline where data flows from grid definition through interpolation to tensor network operations:\n\nStage Module Input Output\nGrid definition QuanticsGrids Domain bounds, R (bits) DiscretizedGrid, InherentDiscreteGrid\nFunction interpolation QuanticsTCI Function + Grid QuanticsTensorCI2\nSimple tensor train SimpleTT TCI result via to_tensor_train() SimpleTensorTrain\nTensor network TreeTN SimpleTT via MPS() MPS / TreeTensorNetwork\nOperators QuanticsTransform MPS + operator Transformed MPS\nTree interpolation TreeTCI Function + tree graph TreeTensorNetwork","title":"Data Flow"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Typical-Pipelines","page":"Modules","text":"","title":"Typical Pipelines"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Quantics-function-interpolation","page":"Modules","text":"QuanticsGrids.DiscretizedGrid → QuanticsTCI.quanticscrossinterpolate\n  → QuanticsTCI.to_tensor_train → SimpleTensorTrain\n  → TreeTN.MPS → MPS operations (truncate!, orthogonalize!, inner, contract)","title":"Quantics function interpolation"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Fourier-analysis-of-interpolated-function","page":"Modules","text":"QuanticsTCI result → MPS\n  → QuanticsTransform.fourier_operator → apply → Fourier-space MPS\n  → TreeTCI.evaluate (at specific k-points)","title":"Fourier analysis of interpolated function"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Affine-coordinate-transform","page":"Modules","text":"MPS → QuanticsTransform.affine_pullback_operator → apply → transformed MPS","title":"Affine coordinate transform"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Tree-structured-interpolation","page":"Modules","text":"TreeTCI.crossinterpolate2 → TreeTensorNetwork\n  → TreeTN operations (contract, truncate!, evaluate)","title":"Tree-structured interpolation"},{"category":"section","location":"modules/#Type-Relationships","page":"Modules","text":"# Chain tensor networks\nTensorTrain = TreeTensorNetwork{Int}  # Primary chain type\nMPS = TensorTrain                      # Alias (no type distinction)\nMPO = TensorTrain                      # Alias (no type distinction)\n\n# MPS-like vs MPO-like is a runtime property:\nis_mps_like(tt)  # each vertex has 1 site index\nis_mpo_like(tt)  # each vertex has 2 site indices (unprimed + primed)","title":"Type Relationships"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#1D-Quantics-Interpolation","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"This tutorial demonstrates how to use Tensor4all.jl to approximate univariate functions in the Quantics Tensor Train (QTT) representation via Tensor Cross Interpolation (TCI).","title":"1D Quantics Interpolation"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#What-is-Quantics-(QTT)-representation?","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"The quantics representation encodes a function defined on a grid of 2^R points as a tensor train with R sites, each having local dimension 2 (one qubit).  The key idea is to write the grid index in binary and assign each bit to a separate tensor site.  Because many physically relevant functions exhibit multi-scale structure that translates into low-rank structure in the quantics representation, the resulting tensor train has small bond dimension – often logarithmic in the number of grid points.\n\nThis makes QTT-based algorithms extremely efficient for functions with features at widely separated scales: oscillations, sharp peaks, slow envelopes, and combinations thereof.","title":"What is Quantics (QTT) representation?"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Setup","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"using Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids   # Grid types and coordinate conversions\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI     # quanticscrossinterpolate, evaluate, integral, ...\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTN          # MPS, orthogonalize!, truncate!, ...","title":"Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Warm-up:-approximating-sin(x)","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"We start with a simple example to illustrate the basic workflow.","title":"Warm-up: approximating sin(x)"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Create-a-quantics-grid","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"DiscretizedGrid maps a continuous interval onto a uniform grid of 2^R points.  The first argument is the number of dimensions (1 for a univariate function), the second is the resolution R, and the third/fourth are vectors giving the lower and upper bounds.\n\nR = 20   # 2^20 ≈ 1 million grid points\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid(1, R, [0.0], [2*pi])","title":"Create a quantics grid"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Run-QTCI","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"quanticscrossinterpolate takes the grid and a callable as its first two positional arguments.  The function f receives one Float64 argument per dimension and must return a Float64.\n\nf_sin(x) = sin(x)\n\nci, ranks, errors = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f_sin; tolerance=1e-10)\n\nThe return values are:\n\nValue Description\nci QuanticsTensorCI2 object – the interpolant\nranks Vector{Int} – maximum bond dimension per TCI sweep\nerrors Vector{Float64} – estimated error per sweep","title":"Run QTCI"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Evaluate-the-interpolant","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"evaluate takes a vector of 1-based grid indices (one per dimension):\n\ni = 42\nval = evaluate(ci, [i])      # value of the interpolant at grid point i\n\nTo convert between grid indices and physical coordinates, use the coordinate conversion functions from QuanticsGrids:\n\nx_vec = grididx_to_origcoord(grid, [i])   # grid index → coordinate vector\nx = x_vec[1]                               # extract the scalar\n\nidx_vec = origcoord_to_grididx(grid, [1.0]) # coordinate → grid index vector\n\nPutting it together to check the approximation quality:\n\nfor i in [1, 100, 2^R]\n    x = grididx_to_origcoord(grid, [i])[1]\n    println(\"x = $x,  QTCI = $(evaluate(ci, [i])),  exact = $(f_sin(x))\")\nend","title":"Evaluate the interpolant"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Compute-the-integral","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"integral(ci) returns the integral over the domain (the sum of all grid values multiplied by the grid spacing):\n\nI_qtci = integral(ci)\nI_exact = -cos(2*pi) + cos(0.0)  # = 0\nprintln(\"QTCI integral: $I_qtci,  exact: $I_exact\")\n\nsum(ci) returns the plain sum of all 2^R function values (without the grid-spacing factor):\n\nS = sum(ci)\n\nThe two are related by integral(ci) ≈ sum(ci) * dx where dx = (upper - lower) / 2^R.","title":"Compute the integral"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Inspect-bond-dimensions","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"println(\"Maximum bond dimension: \", rank(ci))\nprintln(\"Bond dimensions:        \", link_dims(ci))\n\nFor sin(x) with tolerance 1e-10, the maximum bond dimension will typically be quite small (around 5–10), reflecting the low complexity of the function in the quantics representation.","title":"Inspect bond dimensions"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Main-example:-multi-scale-oscillatory-function","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"Now consider a function with structure at vastly different scales – the kind of problem where QTT really shines:\n\nf(x) = e^-xcosBigl(fracxBBigr) qquad B = 2^-30\n\nThe cosine oscillates on a scale of order B approx 10^-9 while the envelope e^-x varies on a scale of order 1.  Resolving both scales on a uniform grid requires sim 2^40 points – over a trillion – yet the QTT representation needs only modest bond dimension.","title":"Main example: multi-scale oscillatory function"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Define-the-function-and-grid","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"B = 2^(-30)\nf(x) = exp(-x) * cos(x / B)\n\nR = 40\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid(1, R, [0.0], [1.0])","title":"Define the function and grid"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Run-QTCI-with-a-bond-dimension-cap","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"You can limit the maximum bond dimension instead of (or in addition to) specifying a tolerance:\n\nci, ranks, errors = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; max_bonddim=15)\n\nOr use a tolerance-based stopping criterion:\n\nci2, ranks2, errors2 = quanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; tolerance=1e-8)\n\ntip: Tip\nWhen you are unsure how large the bond dimension needs to be, start with a tolerance-based run.  Use max_bonddim when you need to control computational cost or memory directly.","title":"Run QTCI with a bond-dimension cap"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Check-the-approximation","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"for i in [1, 2, 3, 2^R]\n    x = grididx_to_origcoord(grid, [i])[1]\n    println(\"x = $x,  QTCI = $(evaluate(ci, [i])),  exact = $(f(x))\")\nend","title":"Check the approximation"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Coordinate-conversions","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"origcoord_to_grididx maps a physical coordinate back to the nearest grid index.  This is useful for probing the interpolant at a specific point in the domain:\n\nx_query = 0.5\ni_vec = origcoord_to_grididx(grid, [x_query])\nval = evaluate(ci, i_vec)\nprintln(\"f($x_query) ≈ $val\")","title":"Coordinate conversions"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Compute-the-integral-2","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"I_qtci = integral(ci)\nprintln(\"Integral via QTCI: $I_qtci\")","title":"Compute the integral"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Inspect-the-TCI-convergence","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"The ranks and errors vectors track the TCI convergence across sweeps. They can be used to verify that the interpolation has converged:\n\nprintln(\"Ranks per sweep:  \", ranks)\nprintln(\"Errors per sweep: \", errors)\nprintln(\"Final bond dimension: \", rank(ci))\nprintln(\"Bond dimensions:      \", link_dims(ci))","title":"Inspect the TCI convergence"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#Converting-to-MPS","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"The QTCI result can be converted to an MPS (a TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) for further tensor-network operations such as orthogonalization, truncation, contraction with other MPS/MPO, etc.\n\nThe conversion is a two-step process: first extract a SimpleTensorTrain, then wrap it as an MPS:\n\ntt = to_tensor_train(ci)   # SimpleTensorTrain\nmps = MPS(tt)              # TreeTensorNetwork{Int}\n\nOnce you have an MPS, the full TreeTN API is available:\n\nprintln(\"Number of sites: \", nv(mps))\nprintln(\"Bond dimensions: \", linkdims(mps))\n\n# Orthogonalize toward site 1\northogonalize!(mps, 1)\n\n# Truncate bond dimensions\ntruncate!(mps; maxdim=10)\nprintln(\"Bond dimensions after truncation: \", linkdims(mps))","title":"Converting to MPS"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/quantics1d/#API-summary","page":"1D Quantics Interpolation","text":"Function Description\nDiscretizedGrid(ndims, R, lo, hi) Create a uniform grid with 2^R points per dimension\nquanticscrossinterpolate(grid, f; tolerance, max_bonddim) Run quantics TCI\nevaluate(ci, [i]) Evaluate the interpolant at 1-based grid index i\nintegral(ci) Integral over the continuous domain\nsum(ci) Sum of all grid-point values\nrank(ci) Maximum bond dimension\nlink_dims(ci) Vector of bond dimensions\ngrididx_to_origcoord(grid, [i]) Grid index to physical coordinate\norigcoord_to_grididx(grid, [x]) Physical coordinate to grid index\nto_tensor_train(ci) Convert QTCI to SimpleTensorTrain\nMPS(tt) Convert SimpleTensorTrain to TreeTensorNetwork{Int}\nnv(mps) Number of vertices\nlinkdims(mps) Bond dimensions of the MPS\northogonalize!(mps, v) Orthogonalize MPS toward vertex v\ntruncate!(mps; maxdim=d) Truncate bond dimensions","title":"API summary"},{"category":"section","location":"api/simplett/#SimpleTT","page":"SimpleTT","text":"","title":"SimpleTT"},{"category":"type","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain","page":"SimpleTT","text":"SimpleTensorTrain{T<:Union{Float64, ComplexF64}}\n\nA simple tensor train (TT/MPS) with statically determined shapes.\n\nSimpleTensorTrain is a simple tensor train library where site dimensions are fixed at construction time.\n\nSupports Float64 and ComplexF64 values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain-Tuple{Vector{<:Integer}, Real}","page":"SimpleTT","text":"SimpleTensorTrain(site_dims::Vector{<:Integer}, value::Real)\n\nCreate a constant tensor train with the given site dimensions and value.\n\nExample\n\ntt = SimpleTensorTrain([2, 3, 4], 1.0)  # All elements equal to 1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Base.copy-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"copy(tt::SimpleTensorTrain)\n\nCreate a deep copy of the tensor train.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.copy"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Base.length-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"length(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> Int\n\nGet the number of sites in the tensor train.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.length"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Base.show-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{IO, Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"show(io::IO, tt::SimpleTensorTrain)\n\nDisplay tensor train information.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Base.sum-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"sum(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> T\n\nCompute the sum over all tensor train elements.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.sum"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Base.zeros-Tuple{Type{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain}, Vector{<:Integer}}","page":"SimpleTT","text":"zeros(::Type{SimpleTensorTrain}, site_dims::Vector{<:Integer})\n\nCreate a zero tensor train with the given site dimensions.\n\nExample\n\ntt = zeros(SimpleTensorTrain, [2, 3, 4])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.zeros"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#LinearAlgebra.norm-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"norm(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> Float64\n\nCompute the Frobenius norm of the tensor train.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"LinearAlgebra.norm"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.compress!-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"compress!(tt::SimpleTensorTrain; method=:LU, tolerance=1e-12, max_bonddim=0)\n\nCompress the tensor train in-place.\n\nMethods: :LU (default), :CI, :SVD.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.compress!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.evaluate-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}, Vector{<:Integer}}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"evaluate(tt::SimpleTensorTrain, indices::Vector{<:Integer}) -> T\n\nEvaluate the tensor train at a given multi-index (0-based indexing).\n\nExample\n\ntt = SimpleTensorTrain([2, 3, 4], 2.0)\nval = evaluate(tt, [0, 1, 2])  # Returns 2.0\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.evaluate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.link_dims-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"link_dims(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> Vector{Int}\n\nGet the link (bond) dimensions. Returns n-1 values for n sites.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.link_dims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.partial_sum-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"partial_sum(tt::SimpleTensorTrain; dims) -> SimpleTensorTrain or scalar\n\nSum over selected dimensions (0-indexed). Returns a new SimpleTensorTrain with the remaining dimensions. If all dimensions are summed, returns the scalar value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.partial_sum"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.rank-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"rank(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> Int\n\nGet the maximum bond dimension (rank).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.rank"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.site_dims-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"site_dims(tt::SimpleTensorTrain) -> Vector{Int}\n\nGet the site (physical) dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.site_dims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/simplett/#Tensor4all.SimpleTT.site_tensor-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain{T}, Integer}} where T","page":"SimpleTT","text":"site_tensor(tt::SimpleTensorTrain, site::Integer) -> Array{T, 3}\n\nGet the site tensor at a specific site (0-based indexing). Returns array with shape (leftdim, sitedim, right_dim).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.SimpleTT.site_tensor"},{"category":"section","location":"api/treetn/#TreeTN-(MPS-/-MPO-/-Tree-Tensor-Networks)","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"","title":"TreeTN (MPS / MPO / Tree Tensor Networks)"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.CanonicalForm","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"CanonicalForm\n\nEnum representing the method used for canonicalization.\n\nUnitary: QR-based canonicalization (tensors are isometric)\nLU: LU-based canonicalization (one factor has unit diagonal)\nCI: Cross Interpolation based canonicalization\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.CanonicalForm"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPO","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPO\n\nType alias for TreeTensorNetwork{Int} (Matrix Product Operator). Vertices are 1-indexed (Julia convention).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPO"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPS\n\nType alias for TreeTensorNetwork{Int} (Matrix Product State). Vertices are 1-indexed (Julia convention).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS-Tuple{Tensor4all.SimpleTT.SimpleTensorTrain}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPS(tt::SimpleTensorTrain)\n\nConvert a SimpleTensorTrain to an MPS by materializing each site tensor and attaching fresh site/link indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS-Tuple{Vector{Tensor}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPS(tensors::Vector{Tensor})\n\nCreate an MPS from a vector of tensors. Vertices are named 1, 2, ..., n (1-indexed). Adjacent tensors must share exactly one common index (the link index).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractArray{T}}, Vector{<:Vector{Index}}}} where T<:Number","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPS(arrays::Vector{<:AbstractArray{T}}, site_inds::Vector{<:Vector{Index}}) where T<:Number\n\nCreate an MPS from arrays and site indices. Link indices are created automatically.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractArray{T}}, Vector{Index}}} where T<:Number","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"MPS(arrays::Vector{<:AbstractArray{T}}, site_inds::Vector{Index}) where T<:Number\n\nConvenience constructor when each tensor has exactly one site index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.MPS"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.TensorTrain","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"TensorTrain\n\nType alias for TreeTensorNetwork{Int}. Same type as MPS and MPO; the distinction is semantic, not type-level.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.TensorTrain"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"TreeTensorNetwork{V}\n\nA tree tensor network with vertices of type V.\n\nWraps a Rust DefaultTreeTN<usize> which supports arbitrary tree topologies. For MPS/MPO, vertices are integers (1-indexed in Julia, 0-indexed in C).\n\nType Parameters\n\nV: Vertex name type. Int for MPS/MPO (1-indexed Julia convention).\n\nConstructors\n\nTreeTensorNetwork{V}(tensors::Vector{Pair{V, Tensor}}) - Create from named tensors\nMPS(tensors::Vector{Tensor}) - Create MPS with vertices 1, 2, ..., n\nMPO(tensors::Vector{Tensor}) - Create MPO with vertices 1, 2, ..., n\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork-Union{Tuple{Array{Pair{V, Tensor}, 1}}, Tuple{V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"TreeTensorNetwork{V}(pairs::Vector{Pair{V, Tensor}}) where V\n\nCreate a TreeTensorNetwork from vertex-name => tensor pairs. Tensors are connected by matching index IDs (einsum rule). C API nodes are named 0, 1, ..., n-1 in the order of the input pairs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Base.:+-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"+(a::TreeTensorNetwork, b::TreeTensorNetwork) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nAdd two tree tensor networks using direct-sum construction.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.:+"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Base.getindex-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"getindex(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v::V) -> Tensor\n\nGet the tensor at vertex v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.getindex"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Base.length-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"length(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Int\n\nGet the number of vertices. Alias for nv.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.length"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Base.setindex!-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Tensor, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"setindex!(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, tensor::Tensor, v::V)\n\nSet the tensor at vertex v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.setindex!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#LinearAlgebra.norm-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"norm(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Float64\n\nCompute the norm of the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"LinearAlgebra.norm"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN._assert_chain-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"_assert_chain(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork)\n\nAssert that a TreeTensorNetwork has chain topology. Used internally by chain-specific operations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN._assert_chain"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN._from_c_vertex-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Integer}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"Convert 0-based C index to Julia vertex name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN._from_c_vertex"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN._to_c_vertex-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"Convert Julia vertex name to 0-based C index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN._to_c_vertex"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.canonical_form-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"canonical_form(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Union{CanonicalForm, Nothing}\n\nGet the canonical form used for the tree tensor network. Returns nothing if no canonical form is set.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.canonical_form"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.findsite-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Any}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"findsite(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork, is)\n\nReturn the first vertex that has common indices with is.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.findsite"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.findsites-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Any}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"findsites(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork, is)\n\nReturn all vertices that have common indices with is.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.findsites"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.inner-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"inner(a::TreeTensorNetwork, b::TreeTensorNetwork) -> ComplexF64\n\nCompute the inner product <a|b>.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.inner"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_chain-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"is_chain(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Bool\n\nCheck if a TreeTensorNetwork has chain (linear) topology.\n\nFor TreeTensorNetwork{Int}, also verifies that vertices are named 1, 2, ..., n in sequential order and that vertex i is connected to vertex i+1.\n\nFor other vertex types, only checks that the topology is a path graph: the graph is connected, has exactly two endpoints for n > 1, and every vertex has degree at most 2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_chain"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_mpo_like-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"is_mpo_like(tt::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) -> Bool\n\nCheck if a chain TensorTrain is MPO-like: each vertex has exactly 2 site indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_mpo_like"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_mps_like-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"is_mps_like(tt::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) -> Bool\n\nCheck if a chain TensorTrain is MPS-like: each vertex has exactly 1 site index.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.is_mps_like"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdim-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}, Integer}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkdim(mps::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}, j::Integer) -> Int\n\nGet the bond dimension between MPS sites j and j+1 (1-indexed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdim"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdim-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkdim(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v1::V, v2::V) -> Int\n\nGet the bond dimension on the edge between vertices v1 and v2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdim"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdims-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkdims(mps::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) -> Vector{Int}\n\nGet all bond dimensions for an MPS-like TTN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkdims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkind-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}, Integer}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkind(mps::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}, j::Integer) -> Index\n\nGet the link index between MPS sites j and j+1 (1-indexed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkind"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkind-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkind(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v1::V, v2::V) -> Index\n\nGet the link (bond) index on the edge between vertices v1 and v2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkind"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkinds-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linkinds(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) -> Vector{Index}\n\nGet all link indices of an MPS-like TTN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linkinds"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.linsolve-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"linsolve(A::TreeTensorNetwork, b::TreeTensorNetwork, x0::TreeTensorNetwork; kwargs...) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nSolve (a0 + a1 * A) * x = b for x using DMRG-like sweeps.\n\nArguments\n\nA: The operator (MPO/TTN operator)\nb: The right-hand side (MPS/TTN state)\nx0: Initial guess (MPS/TTN state)\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\na0::Real=0.0: Coefficient a0\na1::Real=1.0: Coefficient a1\nnsweeps::Integer=10: Number of full sweeps\nrtol::Real=0.0: Relative tolerance\ncutoff::Real=0.0: ITensorMPS.jl cutoff\nmaxdim::Integer=0: Maximum bond dimension\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.linsolve"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.load_mps-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractString}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"load_mps(filepath::AbstractString, name::AbstractString) -> MPS\n\nLoad an MPS from an HDF5 file in ITensorMPS.jl-compatible format.\n\nReturns a TreeTensorNetwork{Int} (MPS) with vertices named 1, 2, ..., n.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.load_mps"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.lognorm-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"lognorm(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Float64\n\nCompute the log-norm of the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.lognorm"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.maxbonddim-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"maxbonddim(mps::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}) -> Int\n\nGet the maximum bond dimension of an MPS-like TTN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.maxbonddim"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.ne-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"ne(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Int\n\nGet the number of edges (bonds) in the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.ne"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.neighbors-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"neighbors(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v::V) -> Vector{V}\n\nGet the neighbors of vertex v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.neighbors"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.nv-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"nv(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Int\n\nGet the number of vertices (nodes) in the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.nv"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.orthogonalize!-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"orthogonalize!(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v::V; form::CanonicalForm=Unitary)\n\nOrthogonalize the tree tensor network in place to vertex v.\n\nArguments\n\nv: Target vertex for orthogonality center\nform: Canonical form to use (default: Unitary)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.orthogonalize!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.orthogonalize-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"orthogonalize(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v::V; form::CanonicalForm=Unitary)\n\nReturn an orthogonalized copy of the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.orthogonalize"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.random_mps-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Type{T}, Vector{Index}}} where T<:Number","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"random_mps([::Type{T},] site_inds::Vector{Index}; linkdims::Union{Integer,Vector{<:Integer}}=1)\n\nConstruct a random MPS with the given site indices and link dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.random_mps"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.rearrange_siteinds-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Vector{Vector{Index}}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"rearrange_siteinds(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork, target_layout::Vector{Vector{Index}};\n                   maxdim::Int=0, rtol::Float64=0.0) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nRearrange site indices so that vertex v holds the indices in target_layout[v]. Returns a new TreeTensorNetwork (the input is not modified).\n\nUses swap_site_indices! internally.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.rearrange_siteinds"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.save_mps-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractString, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"save_mps(filepath::AbstractString, name::AbstractString, mps::TreeTensorNetwork{Int})\n\nSave an MPS to an HDF5 file in ITensorMPS.jl-compatible format.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.save_mps"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.siteind-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{Int64}, Integer}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"siteind(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{Int}, j::Integer) -> Union{Index, Nothing}\n\nGet the first site index at MPS site j (1-indexed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.siteind"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.siteinds-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"siteinds(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork{V}, v::V) -> Vector{Index}\n\nGet the site (physical) indices at vertex v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.siteinds"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.swap_site_indices!-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Dict}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"swap_site_indices!(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork, target::Dict;\n                   maxdim::Int=0, rtol::Float64=0.0)\n\nSwap site indices to a target vertex assignment. The tensor network values are preserved via SVD factorization along each edge.\n\ntarget maps id(index) (as UInt64) to target vertex number (1-based).\n\nArguments\n\ntarget: mapping from index ID to target vertex\nmaxdim: maximum bond dimension after SVD (0 = no limit)\nrtol: relative SVD truncation tolerance (0.0 = no truncation)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.swap_site_indices!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.to_dense-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"to_dense(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Tensor\n\nConvert the tree tensor network to a dense tensor by contracting all link indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.to_dense"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.truncate!-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"truncate!(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork; rtol=0.0, cutoff=0.0, maxdim=0)\n\nTruncate the tree tensor network bond dimensions in-place.\n\nArguments\n\nrtol: Relative tolerance for truncation (0.0 = not set)\ncutoff: ITensorMPS.jl cutoff (0.0 = not set). Converted to rtol = sqrt(cutoff).\nmaxdim: Maximum bond dimension (0 = no limit)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.truncate!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.truncate-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"truncate(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork; rtol=0.0, cutoff=0.0, maxdim=0) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nReturn a truncated copy of the tree tensor network.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.truncate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.TreeTN.vertices-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}}, Tuple{V}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"vertices(ttn::TreeTensorNetwork) -> Vector{V}\n\nGet all vertex names.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTN.vertices"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetn/#Tensor4all.contract-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork{V}}} where V","page":"TreeTN (MPS/MPO)","text":"contract(a::TreeTensorNetwork, b::TreeTensorNetwork; kwargs...) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nContract two tree tensor networks.\n\nArguments\n\nmethod: Contraction method - :zipup (default), :fit, or :naive\nmaxdim: Maximum bond dimension (0 for no limit)\nrtol: Relative tolerance (0.0 = not set)\ncutoff: ITensorMPS.jl cutoff (0.0 = not set)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.contract"},{"category":"section","location":"api/treetci/#TreeTCI","page":"TreeTCI","text":"","title":"TreeTCI"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci","page":"TreeTCI","text":"SimpleTreeTci{T<:Union{Float64, ComplexF64}}(local_dims, graph)\n\nStateful TreeTCI object for tree-structured tensor cross interpolation.\n\nArguments\n\nlocal_dims::Vector{Int}: Local dimension at each site (length = graph.n_sites)\ngraph::TreeTciGraph: Tree graph structure\n\nLifecycle\n\ntci = SimpleTreeTci([2, 2, 2, 2], graph)\nadd_global_pivots!(tci, [zeros(Int, 4)])\nfor _ in 1:20\n    sweep!(tci, f; tolerance=1e-8)\n    max_bond_error(tci) < 1e-8 && break\nend\nttn = to_treetn(tci, f)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci"},{"category":"type","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.TreeTciGraph","page":"TreeTCI","text":"TreeTciGraph(n_sites, edges)\n\nDefine a tree graph structure for TreeTCI.\n\nArguments\n\nn_sites::Int: Number of sites\nedges::Vector{Tuple{Int,Int}}: Edge list (0-based site indices)\n\nExamples\n\n# Linear chain: 0-1-2-3\ngraph = TreeTciGraph(4, [(0, 1), (1, 2), (2, 3)])\n\n# Star graph: 0 at center\ngraph = TreeTciGraph(4, [(0, 1), (0, 2), (0, 3)])\n\n# 7-site branching tree\ngraph = TreeTciGraph(7, [(0, 1), (1, 2), (1, 3), (3, 4), (4, 5), (4, 6)])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.TreeTciGraph"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI._evaluate_batch-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Vector{UInt64}, Int64, Int64}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Internal: call C API evaluate using IndexId-based interface and return typed results.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI._evaluate_batch"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI._treetci_batch_trampoline-Tuple{Ptr{UInt64}, UInt64, UInt64, Ptr{Float64}, Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Internal trampoline for f64 batch callbacks.\n\nThe user function signature is: f(batch::Matrix{Csize_t}) -> Vector{Float64} where batch is column-major (n_sites, n_points) with 0-based indices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI._treetci_batch_trampoline"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI._treetci_batch_trampoline_c64-Tuple{Ptr{UInt64}, UInt64, UInt64, Ptr{Float64}, Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Internal trampoline for c64 batch callbacks.\n\nThe user function signature is: f(batch::Matrix{Csize_t}) -> Vector{ComplexF64} where batch is column-major (n_sites, n_points) with 0-based indices. Results are written as interleaved doubles.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI._treetci_batch_trampoline_c64"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.add_global_pivots!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}, Vector{Vector{Int64}}}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"add_global_pivots!(tci, pivots)\n\nAdd global pivots. Each pivot is a full multi-index over all sites (0-based).\n\nArguments\n\ntci::SimpleTreeTci\npivots::Vector{Vector{Int}}: Each element has length n_sites, 0-based indices\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.add_global_pivots!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.bond_dims-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Bond dimensions (ranks) at each edge.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.bond_dims"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.crossinterpolate2-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Type{T}, Any, Union{NTuple{N, Integer}, Vector{<:Integer}}, Tensor4all.TreeTCI.TreeTciGraph}} where {T<:Union{Float64, ComplexF64}, N}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"crossinterpolate2([T], f, localdims, graph; kwargs...) -> (tci, ranks, errors)\n\nRun TreeTCI to convergence on a tree graph.\n\nThe sweep loop runs in Julia, printing convergence info when verbosity > 0. This matches the API style of TensorCrossInterpolation.crossinterpolate2.\n\nArguments\n\nT: Scalar type (Float64 or ComplexF64). Inferred if omitted.\nf: Batch evaluation function — f(batch) -> Vector{T} where batch is a Matrix{Csize_t} of shape (n_sites, n_points) in column-major layout. batch[i, j] is the 0-based local index at site i for evaluation point j. The function must return a Vector of length n_points.\nlocaldims::Union{Vector{Int}, NTuple{N,Int}}: Local dimensions at each site\ngraph::TreeTciGraph: Tree graph structure\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\ninitialpivots::Vector{Vector{Int}} = [zeros(Int, n)]: Initial pivots (0-based)\ntolerance::Float64 = 1e-8: Target tolerance\nmaxbonddim::Int = typemax(Int): Maximum bond dimension\nmaxiter::Int = 20: Maximum sweeps\nverbosity::Int = 0: 0=silent, 1=summary per loginterval, 2=bond dims and timing\nloginterval::Int = 10: Print every N iterations (when verbosity >= 1)\nnormalizeerror::Bool = true: Normalize error by max sample value\nproposer::Symbol = :default: :default, :simple, or :truncated_default\ncenter_site::Int = 0: Materialization center site (0-based)\n\nReturns\n\ntci::SimpleTreeTci{T}: The converged TCI state (call to_treetn(tci, f) to materialize)\nranks::Vector{Int}: Max rank per iteration\nerrors::Vector{Float64}: (Normalized) error per iteration\n\nExample\n\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTCI\n\n# Define a star graph: site 0 connected to sites 1,2,3,4\ngraph = TreeTciGraph(5, [(0,1), (0,2), (0,3), (0,4)])\n\n# Batch evaluation function (0-based indices)\nfunction f(batch)\n    n_sites, n_pts = size(batch)\n    [prod(batch[i, j] + 1.0 for i in 1:n_sites) for j in 1:n_pts]\nend\n\n# Run TCI\ntci, ranks, errors = crossinterpolate2(f, fill(3, 5), graph;\n    tolerance=1e-10, verbosity=1)\n\n# Materialize to TreeTensorNetwork\nttn = to_treetn(tci, f)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.crossinterpolate2"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, AbstractMatrix{<:Integer}}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"evaluate(ttn, batch::AbstractMatrix{<:Integer}) -> Vector\n\nEvaluate a TreeTensorNetwork at multiple multi-indices given as a matrix. batch has shape (n_sites, n_points) — the rightmost dimension is the batch index. Indices are 0-based.\n\nExample\n\nbatch = [0 1; 1 0; 2 1; 0 1]  # 4 sites, 2 points\nvals = evaluate(ttn, batch)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate-Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Vector{<:Integer}}","page":"TreeTCI","text":"evaluate(ttn, indices::Vector{<:Integer}) -> T\n\nEvaluate a TreeTensorNetwork at a single multi-index (0-based). Returns a scalar (Float64 or ComplexF64 depending on storage).\n\nExample\n\nval = evaluate(ttn, [0, 1, 2, 0])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork, Array{Vector{T}, 1}}} where T<:Integer","page":"TreeTCI","text":"evaluate(ttn, indices::Vector{Vector{<:Integer}}) -> Vector\n\nEvaluate a TreeTensorNetwork at multiple multi-indices (0-based). Each element of indices is a multi-index of length n_sites.\n\nExample\n\nvals = evaluate(ttn, [[0,1,2,0], [1,0,1,1]])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.evaluate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_bond_error-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Maximum bond error across all edges.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_bond_error"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_rank-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Maximum rank (bond dimension) across all edges.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_rank"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_sample_value-Union{Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"Maximum observed sample value (for normalization).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.max_sample_value"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.sweep!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}, Any}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"sweep!(tci, f; proposer=:default, tolerance=1e-8, max_bond_dim=0)\n\nRun one optimization iteration (visit all edges once).\n\nArguments\n\ntci::SimpleTreeTci\nf: Batch evaluation function f(batch::Matrix{Csize_t}) -> Vector{T} where batch is column-major (n_sites, n_points) with 0-based indices\nproposer: :default, :simple, or :truncated_default\ntolerance: Relative tolerance\nmax_bond_dim: Maximum bond dimension (0 = unlimited)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.sweep!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/treetci/#Tensor4all.TreeTCI.to_treetn-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Tensor4all.TreeTCI.SimpleTreeTci{T}, Any}} where T","page":"TreeTCI","text":"to_treetn(tci, f; center_site=0)\n\nConvert converged TreeTCI state to a TreeTensorNetwork.\n\nArguments\n\ntci::SimpleTreeTci: Converged state\nf: Batch evaluation function (same as sweep!)\ncenter_site: BFS root site for materialization (0-based)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.TreeTCI.to_treetn"},{"category":"section","location":"api/quanticstransform/#QuanticsTransform","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"","title":"QuanticsTransform"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.AffineParams","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"AffineParams(a, b)\n\nAffine pullback parameters representing f(y) = g(A*y + b).\n\na: source-dimension by output-dimension affine matrix\nb: source-dimension shift vector\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.AffineParams"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.BoundaryCondition","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"BoundaryCondition\n\nBoundary condition for quantics operators.\n\nPeriodic (0): Periodic boundary conditions\nOpen (1): Open boundary conditions\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.BoundaryCondition"},{"category":"type","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.LinearOperator","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"LinearOperator\n\nA linear operator that can be applied to a tree tensor network (MPS).\n\nWraps a Rust LinearOperator from the quantics transform crate. Created via operator construction functions like shift_operator, flip_operator, etc.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.LinearOperator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.affine_operator-Tuple{Integer, AbstractMatrix{<:Integer}, AbstractMatrix{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"affine_operator(r::Integer, a_num::AbstractMatrix{<:Integer}, a_den::AbstractMatrix{<:Integer},\n                b_num::AbstractVector{<:Integer}, b_den::AbstractVector{<:Integer}; bc) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate an affine transform with rational coefficients on quantized coordinates. bc must contain one boundary condition per output variable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.affine_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.affine_pullback_operator-Tuple{Integer, Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.AffineParams}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"affine_pullback_operator(r::Integer, params::AffineParams;\n                         bc=fill(Periodic, source_ndims(params))) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate an affine pullback operator implementing f(y) = g(A*y + b).\n\nThe input state has source_ndims(params) variables and the output state has output_ndims(params) variables. Boundary conditions apply to the transformed source coordinates A*y + b.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.affine_pullback_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.apply-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.LinearOperator, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"apply(op::LinearOperator, state::TreeTensorNetwork; method=:naive, rtol=0.0, maxdim=0) -> TreeTensorNetwork\n\nApply a linear operator to a tree tensor network (MPS).\n\nArguments\n\nop: Linear operator\nstate: Input MPS/TreeTN\nmethod: Contraction method - :naive, :zipup, or :fit\nrtol: Relative tolerance (0.0 = default)\nmaxdim: Maximum bond dimension (0 = unlimited)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.apply"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.binaryop_operator-NTuple{5, Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"binaryop_operator(r::Integer, a1::Integer, b1::Integer, a2::Integer, b2::Integer;\n                  bc1=Periodic, bc2=Periodic) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a two-output binary operator corresponding to (a1*x + b1*y, a2*x + b2*y).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.binaryop_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.cumsum_operator-Tuple{Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"cumsum_operator(r::Integer) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a cumulative sum operator: yi = sum{j<i} x_j.\n\nArguments\n\nr: Number of quantics bits\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.cumsum_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.flip_operator-Tuple{Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"flip_operator(r::Integer; bc=Periodic) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a flip operator: f(x) = g(2^r - x).\n\nArguments\n\nr: Number of quantics bits\nbc: Boundary condition (Periodic or Open)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.flip_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.flip_operator_multivar-Tuple{Integer, Integer, Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"flip_operator_multivar(r::Integer, nvariables::Integer, target_var::Integer; bc=Periodic) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a flip operator acting on one variable in a multi-variable quantics system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.flip_operator_multivar"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.fourier_operator-Tuple{Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"fourier_operator(r::Integer; forward=true, maxbonddim=0, tolerance=0.0) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a Quantics Fourier Transform operator.\n\nArguments\n\nr: Number of quantics bits\nforward: true for forward FT, false for inverse\nmaxbonddim: Maximum bond dimension (0 = default of 12)\ntolerance: Tolerance for FT construction (0.0 = default of 1e-14)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.fourier_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.phase_rotation_operator-Tuple{Integer, Real}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"phase_rotation_operator(r::Integer, theta::Real) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a phase rotation operator: f(x) = exp(ithetax) * g(x).\n\nArguments\n\nr: Number of quantics bits\ntheta: Phase angle\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.phase_rotation_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.phase_rotation_operator_multivar-Tuple{Integer, Real, Integer, Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"phase_rotation_operator_multivar(r::Integer, theta::Real, nvariables::Integer, target_var::Integer) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a phase rotation operator acting on one variable in a multi-variable quantics system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.phase_rotation_operator_multivar"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_input_space!-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.LinearOperator, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"set_input_space!(op::LinearOperator, state::TreeTensorNetwork) -> LinearOperator\n\nReset the operator's true input site indices to match state.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_input_space!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_iospaces!","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"set_iospaces!(op::LinearOperator, input_state::TreeTensorNetwork, output_state::TreeTensorNetwork=input_state) -> LinearOperator\n\nReset the operator's true input and output site indices to match the given states.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_iospaces!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_output_space!-Tuple{Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.LinearOperator, Tensor4all.TreeTN.TreeTensorNetwork}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"set_output_space!(op::LinearOperator, state::TreeTensorNetwork) -> LinearOperator\n\nReset the operator's true output site indices to match state.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.set_output_space!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.shift_operator-Tuple{Integer, Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"shift_operator(r::Integer, offset::Integer; bc=Periodic) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a shift operator: f(x) = g(x + offset) mod 2^r.\n\nArguments\n\nr: Number of quantics bits\noffset: Shift offset (can be negative)\nbc: Boundary condition (Periodic or Open)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.shift_operator"},{"category":"method","location":"api/quanticstransform/#Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.shift_operator_multivar-NTuple{4, Integer}","page":"QuanticsTransform","text":"shift_operator_multivar(r::Integer, offset::Integer, nvariables::Integer, target_var::Integer; bc=Periodic) -> LinearOperator\n\nCreate a shift operator acting on one variable in a multi-variable quantics system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tensor4all.QuanticsTransform.shift_operator_multivar"},{"category":"section","location":"#Tensor4all.jl","page":"Home","text":"A Julia wrapper for tensor4all-rs, providing tensor network operations via C FFI.","title":"Tensor4all.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Features","page":"Home","text":"Index & Tensor: Named indices with tags, prime levels, and automatic contraction\nSimpleTT: Simple tensor trains with fixed site dimensions\nTreeTN (MPS/MPO): Tree tensor networks — MPS, MPO, and general tree topologies\nQuanticsGrids: Coordinate transforms between physical grids and quantics (binary) representation\nQuanticsTCI: Tensor cross interpolation in quantics representation\nQuanticsTransform: Fourier, shift, flip, phase rotation, and affine operators on MPS\nTreeTCI: TCI on arbitrary tree topologies","title":"Features"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using Tensor4all\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsGrids\nusing Tensor4all.QuanticsTCI\nusing Tensor4all.TreeTN\n\n# Interpolate a function on a quantics grid\nR = 20  # 2^20 grid points\ngrid = DiscretizedGrid{1}(R, 0.0, 1.0)\nf(x) = exp(-10x) * cos(100x)\nci, ranks, errors = quanticscrossinterpolate(Float64, f, grid; tolerance=1e-8)\n\n# Convert to MPS for further operations\ntt = to_tensor_train(ci)\nmps = MPS(tt)\n\nSee the tutorials section in the sidebar for cross-module workflows.","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/tensor4all/Tensor4all.jl\")\n\nThe Rust backend (libtensor4all_capi) is built automatically during Pkg.build().","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Module-Overview","page":"Home","text":"See Module Architecture for the dependency graph and data flow.","title":"Module Overview"}]
}
